Dia. 02 If White Plays
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fswiss\fcharset0 Tahoma;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White played the hane and connection with 1 and 3.
\par
\par Now it can't be counted as\lang1033\f1  though\lang1042\f0  Black plays at A and White plays at B.
\par This case is different because Black\lang1033\f1 's \lang1042\f0 hane on the first line is got\lang1033\f1 e, while\lang1042\f0  White\lang1033\f1 's\lang1042\f0  hane is sente.
\par
\par
\par }
